Teaming up with my friends at @Amoretti to bring y’all the ultimate butter pecan cake! #ad It’s flavored with browned butter, plenty of pecans, and Amoretti’s Butter Pecan Artisan flavoring. Which means it’s super flavorful and so perfect for the holidays! Check out the recipe below! #AmorettiBaking #sponsored 
 
PRALINE SAUCE:
¼ cup unsalted butter, diced
¼ cup packed dark brown sugar
2 tbsp heavy cream
Pinch salt
½ tsp vanilla
¼ cup finely chopped pecans
 
FOR THE CAKE:
1 cup browned butter, room temperature
1 ½ cups sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tbsp Amoretti’s Butter Pecan Artisan Flavoring
3 large eggs
2 cups all-purpose flour
1 tbsp baking powder
½ tsp salt
1 cup whole milk
1 cup finely chopped pecans
 
FOR THE FROSTING:
1 cup unsalted butter, room temp
1 cup shortening
2 tbsp Amoretti’s Butter Pecan Artisan Flavoring
2 tbsp heavy cream
4 cups powdered sugar
 
Praline sauce: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat. Add dark brown sugar and whisk continuously until sugar melts and mixture begins to boil, about 5 minutes. Stir in cream, vanilla, salt. Let sauce cool completely.
 
Cake:
1. Preheat oven to 350°F. Butter and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
2. In a large bowl, cream browned butter and sugar with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, vanilla, and butter pecan flavoring. Mix until just blended.
3. Add flour, baking powder, salt, and milk. Mix until combined, about 1 minute. Stir in pecans.
4. Divide batter between cake pans. Bake for 23-25 mins or until cakes are set in the center. 
5. Let cakes cool in pans 10 to 15 minutes; to a wire rack to cool completely.
 
Frosting:
1. Cream butter and shortening on medium speed in the bowl of a stand mixer with the paddle attachment. Add butter pecan flavoring; mix well.
2. Add half of the powdered sugar and the cream. Mix on medium low until mostly combined, then medium-high speed until completely combined. Repeat with second half of powdered sugar.
 
Assembly: Place one cake layer on a plate. Spread frosting over the top. Place the second layer on top of that. Spread frosting over the top and around the sides. Spread praline sauce over the top and sprinkle with pecans. Enjoy!

Teaming up with my friends at @amoretti (#ad) again to bring you these decadent bakery-style Chocolate Espresso Cookies! Using Amoretti’s Espresso Artisan Flavoring means these cookies are rich, delicious, and full of coffee flavor. Thick, chewy, chocolaty, and SO good! #amorettibaking #sponsored
 
½ cup unsalted butter, room temperature
½ cup packed light brown sugar
¼ cup white granulated sugar
1 large egg
1 tsp vanilla extract
2 tbsp Amoretti Espresso Artisan Flavoring
1 ¼ cup all-purpose flour
½ cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 tsp cornstarch
½ tsp baking powder
½ tsp baking soda
½ tsp salt
1 ½ cups chocolate chips
 
Preheat oven to 350°F and line 2-3 baking sheets with parchment paper. In the bowl of a stand mixer, cream butter and both sugars until light and fluffy. Add the egg; mix well. Add vanilla and Espresso flavoring. In another bowl, whisk together flour, cocoa powder, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Add to the mixture in the stand mixer bowl. Mix until all ingredients are incorporated and the dough comes together. Add chocolate chips; mix well. Scoop cookies (I used 1-inch scoop)  onto the prepared baking sheets about 1-2 inches apart. Bake 8-10 minutes or until set in the center and crackled around the top. Cool 10-15 minutes. Enjoy!
